text:
Dec 23, 24
• Explored Metabase interface and navigated through existing dashboards
• Reviewed table documentation to understand core entities and relationships
• Reviewed SQL behind existing cards to understand joins and aggregations

Dec 26
• Practiced creating cards using joins, filters, and summarize metrics
• Analyzed existing dashboards to understand metric selection and layout
Dec 29
• Built a practice dashboard using the Metabase sample database.
• Gained clarity on selecting appropriate metrics, summarize options, and visualizations for KPI cards
• Submitted the practice dashboard for review and awaiting further tasks

Dec 30
Started working on the newly assigned dashboard .
Explored the database , identified relevant tables, and implemented a few initial KPI cards.
Attended the weekly review call

DEC 31st

• Continued working on the dashboard and finalized the relevant KPIs and tables.
• Build and finalized key visualizations focused on facility level insights and submitted the dashboard for review.

Jan 1
• Practiced building some more KPI cards and visualizations.
• Tried different charts and arrangements for the dashboard

Jan 2
• Recieved review feedback on the submitted dashboard and completed the suggested changes.
•Cleaned up visualizations and improved card names.

Next
Work on newly assigned task.

Jan 5th
•Explored care instance to understand overall flow and tried
adding some patients and encounters.
•Completed the assigned task and submitted.
•Worked on the required changes based on the feedback.
•Had a call to clarify some doubts and learned to implement
click behaviour correctly in dashboards.
